1. A New York law firm filed a class action lawsuit against Strategy, accusing it of misleading investors to disclose the profitability of its Bitcoin strategy;
2. Binance Alpha has launched MemeCore (M);
3. China Asset Management Hong Kong: exploring the integrated application of stablecoins for payment, redemption, and asset management;
4. Speaker of the U.S. House of Representatives: The final vote on the "Big and Beautiful Act" will be held at 20:00 today;
5. Arthur Hayes: Stablecoins are a "new weapon" for finance, and may bring trillions of dollars of liquidity support to Bitcoin in the future;
6. Wallets suspected to be related to Matrixport have withdrawn more than 30,000 ETH in total;
7. Bitstamp, a subsidiary of Robinhood, has obtained a Singapore MAS license;
8. Binance Alpha has added a pre-detection mechanism for rush purchases, and face verification can be exempted within 30 minutes if the pre-detection is passed;
9. The "Insider Whale" has once again lost $381,000 in liquidation, and the remaining short orders are still on the verge of liquidation;
10. GMGN launches a video version of the profit chart function, which supports the generation of MP4 within 10 seconds Format.
